The <b>Yucatan Poorwill</b> (<i>Nyctiphrynus yucatanicus</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nightjar" title="Nightjar">nightjar</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caprimulgidae" title="Caprimulgidae" class="mw-redirect">Caprimulgidae</a> family. It is found in the entire <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yucat%C3%A1n_Peninsula" title="Yucatán Peninsula">Yucatán Peninsula</a> region except on the north coast, in a 50&nbsp;km wide coastal strip that extends 700&nbsp;km; the species ranges to south-central <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belize" title="Belize">Belize</a>, northeasternmost <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala" title="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, and southern regions <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrubland" title="Shrubland">shrubland</a>.
